agicianstower>Istaron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 194<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/03 8:45:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1120.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Great Divide</span><hr size=1> Great Divide is the best place to do this absolutely solo.  They don't give as large of faction hits here as they do in Kael, but the quantity more than makes up for it.  You can kill literally hundreds per hour.  Take the whole fort and every roamer you see.  You should be finished in a few days of 2-3 hour sessions (you can test your faction on the named wurm in the caves).<br>
<br>
Threatening will go very fast.  Threatening to ally takes about the same faction work as max-KOS to threatening.  When you hit dubious in GD, go to SS and hand in the heads/toes you have looted.  This will probably jump you to indifferent or amiable (maybe even warmly if you have been lucky).<br>
<br>
This is how I did it, a year and a half ago, and I had to fight for spawns with other faction hunters.  These days, there aren't nearly as many people working on CoV faction, so I imagine you can get a goodly number of the giants in GD. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=llador1>Llador1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/03 12:39:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1120.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: the quest for the solo magician to improve cov faction..</span><hr size=1> I got my CoV faction up by soloing in EW and one Kael raid There are 3 Ogre Mercenaries at P401, N159 which can be single pulled. Occasionally a named pops which wasn't any trouble to my 51 pet.  Each kill gives CoV faction and a few pp and xp too. They are on a 30min approx timer so you can pull the Kromrif Prison guards (lvl 37 - lots of hp) in the surrounding huts. Do NOT pull the named (think its Warden something - been a while) as even pulling him will trigger a death squad. You can set up camp just to the west but a little from the base of the cliff. There are no wandering giants but there is a lot of other stuff you have to watch for. Ulthorks(lvl 31-36) and walruses (lv 29-36) will attack you. Wooly Rhino's (lvl 35-41) wont. Turn in any toes and helmets to Lt Milvern in Skyshrine (SS) but you need to get your CoV faction up to apprehensive at least before you can go in SS and at least kindly for the quests, so it kind of defeats the object but you do get a few pp and faction raises for each turn in.<br>
<br>
The Mercenaries drop an Assignment and Mercenary Brooch.  You apparently used to be able to turn in the Assignments to one of the guards but this appears to have been nerfed with the SS zone change. The Brooch'es are turned into Torm Wenrar in SS although I have not done this quest so don't know what the reward is. As with all SS quests you have to con at least kindly. <p>&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.carl.skepper.btinternet.co.uk/guild/Images/madmage.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;Llador - Mage&lt;br&gt;also:&lt;br&gt;Mulani (Druid)&lt;br&gt;Tzuni (Enchanter)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eendyarsoulseeker>Eendyar Soulseeker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(1/22/03 1:49:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1120.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Solo Mage CoV Faction increases</span><hr size=1> Again as stated Statue and Vindi or AoW good faction hits, Solo or not you can hang in Kael ( you will be there soloing for faction any how) If a Raid is going on Just Follow them and load up your lvl 1 Burst of Flame spell ( has like a 2 second Cast time ) They will be pulling alot of Bigger mobs from the Arena to Get Vindi, Statue AoW, etc etc..... Just hang in there with their grp of peeps far behind them so you not in way. When they pull Named Big mob out of Arena ( Vindi, Statue, AoW) Wait until they are engaged Run up and hit them with your lvl 1 spell ( Resisted or not you got hate so you will get faction when he dies.) From that point just hang out and wait for him to die. Get faction boom Instant raise .. Woot. <br>
<br>
<br>
In the mean time just solo in Kael Some where. Like Stated again you can join a ring war and hit them with your 2 second lvl 1 Burst flame spell one by one. As they Fall one by one you get faction. Or if you see grps fighting giants hit with the lvl one spell. Think of it as the bow and arrow Rangers use to hit mobs for faction except yours is a flame spell =p<br>
<br>
<br>
PS.. The Idol that spawns the AoW does not give Faction .. ( Idol only tho ) <p>----------------<br>
